  "text": "The consumer offset commit flow in Apache Kafka begins when an application calls KafkaConsumer.commitSync() in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/KafkaConsumer.java (line 940). This method delegates to a ConsumerDelegate instance.\n\nFor the classic consumer group protocol, ClassicKafkaConsumer.commitSync() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ClassicKafkaConsumer.java, line 741) is called, which invokes ConsumerCoordinator.commitOffsetsSync() with the offsets and a timer.\n\nConsumerCoordinator.commitOffsetsSync() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerCoordinator.java, line 1140) sends an OffsetCommitRequest to the broker by calling sendOffsetCommitRequest() (line 1270). This method constructs an OffsetCommitRequest and sends it to the group coordinator broker using client.send().\n\nOn the broker side, GroupCoordinatorService.commitOffsets() (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorService.java, line 1971) receives the request. It schedules a write operation that calls GroupCoordinatorShard.commitOffset() (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorShard.java, line 852).\n\nGroupCoordinatorShard.commitOffset() delegates to OffsetMetadataManager.commitOffset() (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetMetadataManager.java, line 600), which validates the offset commit request and creates CoordinatorRecord objects using GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.newOffsetCommitRecord() (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.java, line 467). This helper creates records with OffsetCommitKey and OffsetCommitValue structures that represent the offset state.\n\nThese CoordinatorRecord objects are then processed by CoordinatorRuntime.append() (coordinator-common/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/common/runtime/CoordinatorRuntime.java, line 948), which batches the records into a MemoryRecordsBuilder. When the batch is full or the linger timeout expires, CoordinatorRuntime.flushCurrentBatch() (line 779) is called, which invokes partitionWriter.append() (line 795) to write the batched records to the __consumer_offsets topic partition in the broker's log.\n\nThe complete chain shows the offset commit traveling from the consumer client through the coordinator protocol to the broker's group coordinator, which validates and persists the offset state to the __consumer_offsets internal topic."
}

